						               													<description>In Ruby Rush, the players represent prospectors trying to cash in on a sudden up-cropping of rubies in the nearby landscape, while deterring the opposition.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The deck is 26 cards, and every card has a ruby value.  Most of the cards are action cards that allow players to &amp;quot;Dig&amp;quot; up more cards, steal from other players, etc.  Being too greedy can result in a cave-in, eliminating the player from the game.  When the deck is exhausted, the remaining players total their rubies, and the highest value wins; or if all but one player is eliminated, that player wins immediately.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The skill sets involved are risk management, and to a lesser degree, card-counting and bluffing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game rules include a variant for 4-5 players with the addition of another set of cards with the same game play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
